### Local development example environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill values. Do NOT commit your real `.env` to git.

# -------------------------
# Postgres container (docker-compose) - example
# -------------------------
# These values are used by the postgres service in `docker-compose.yml`.
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres
POSTGRES_DB=auth

# -------------------------
# Spring datasource (application)
# -------------------------
# When running the Spring Boot app on your host (IDE or `./gradlew bootRun`),
# connect to the database at `localhost` (the host port mapped by compose):
# Recommended for running the app on your host:
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/auth
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=postgres
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=postgres

# If you change the port mapping in `docker-compose.yml` (e.g. hostPort:containerPort
# like `5433:5432`), update the JDBC URL accordingly (e.g. `jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/auth`).

# -------------------------
# JWT configuration
# -------------------------
# Provide a long random secret for signing JWTs. The app reads JWT_SECRET from the
# environment or from a `.env` file. Do NOT commit real
# secrets to version control. Example (replace with a secure secret):
JWT_SECRET=9f2d4a6b8c3e7f1a2b4c6d8e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7098ab1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0

